reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Heavy duty belt with infinite adjustability
reviews.reviewText: This is a great belt, it adjusts to any size and holds securely.The quick release buckle speeds the process of getting the belt opened up and it re-attaches quickly back to its proper adjustment. It's a good value for the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It's perfect, exactly what I was expecting
reviews.reviewText: This is the perfect belt for duty, personally I am a firefighter and needed a new belt for my uniform and this was easy from start to finish. Sizing is absolutely accurate and is really heavy duty, I was expecting a bit lighter quality but it's very sturdy and I feel confident I got the best belt for the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Good quality belt. Looks good and holds the pants up. Does not clear metal detector.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very nice and durable for the price
reviews.reviewText: For the price, you would be hard pressed to find a better belt out there for work, tactical or just casual. My only complaint (very small), the ends of the belt don't fit through most of my belt loops so, I have to take the one end off just about every time. That said, if i use it for work and have a lot of things on my belt (cell, Gerber, tape measure), it doesn't pull through when I unbuckle.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Finally a Belt Made For Me
reviews.reviewText: I love how sturdy this Belt is Made. I am a very large man with a large Belly, so finding a good Belt that I can fasten under my belly is hard for me. I am an outdoors man and need something strong to hold the gear or shooting bag, this Belt is definitely it. It fits great, it's made with good strong material & best of all the Latch is so easy for me to fasten & release. I am a permanent customer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I got this Belt to use with my Glocks to get more practice. Very nice and I really like the buckle , very positive design

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Buckle to big
reviews.reviewText: Quality made product wish it worked, but the belt buckle would not fit through belt loops.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars it's a solid belt
reviews.reviewText: I got collars for my puppy that have this style buckle. I was impressed with it so I found belts for myself that have the simplified buckle. the buckle only matters for "off". I need to undo the belt from the buckle and thread the belt through the loops and then adjust for fit. which is pretty great. leather belts have fixed holes so you don't get exact comfort. it can be a bit tight or a bit loose. neither is good if you are carrying.I typically have a 4" blade camel bone skinner horizontal over my left pocket. a 238 at 3 O'clock, and a snacky bag full of treats when I play with my puppy. no sagging yet. this belt is a bit more thin than the leather so I am not overly confident in the IWB style clip on my holster.

Product correctly delivered in short leadtime. Product looks are sturdy and heavy-duty, you can wear in good comfort, very though belt !My only "-" point would be the velcro strip attached, this ought to be a little bit longer to accommodate fully correct waist adjustment as this very thoughtfull application of velcro-on-belt keeps the belt very nice in place.Also very nice touch is the separate belt-clip/hook delivered with the belt. Nice gesture and practical !

reviews.reviewTitle: MOZETO Taktischer Gürtel mit Schnellspanner und Metallschnalle
reviews.reviewText: Ich bin mit dem Gürtel super zufrieden.Der Gürtel ist besonders schnell zu öffnen, bzw. zu schließen.Die Schnalle passt durch die meisten Gürtelschlaufen nicht durch.Deshalb muß man zuerst einmal den Gürtel ohne den rechten Verschluss einfädeln.Danach bleibt der Gürtel einfach an der Hose.Der Wechsel auf eine andere Hose, also auch das erneute Einfädeln dauert nicht so lange.Die Verbindung der Gürtelschnalle ist sehr stabil und rastet mit hörbaren Klack sauber ein.Verschluss und Beschichtung sind sehr gut verarbeitetDer Gürtel ist ebenfalls sehr stabil und trotzdem flexibel.Durch das Befestigungssystem der Schnalle lässt sich die Gürtellänge sehr einfach einstellen/anpassen.Insgesamt sind alle Einzelteile des Gürtels qualitativ hochwertig und einwandfrei verarbeitet.Es gab keinerlei Kritikpunkte oder Mängel.
Cinturón tosco, bueno y de calidad, hebilla de metal y el cinturon no es muy delgado y bastante grueso, se ve resistente y muy bueno, recomendado.
